    "### 1.3 What is Predictive Modeling?\n",
    "\n",
    "Predictive modeling is the process of using statistical algorithms and machine learning techniques to forecast future outcomes based on historical data. After we complete EDA and understand our dataset, we use the cleaned and prepared data to train machine learning models that can predict outcomes for new, unseen data.\n",
    "\n",
    "For example: Given information about a restaurant customer (their age, gender, preferred cuisine, alcohol habits), can we predict the rating they would give to a restaurant? This is the kind of question predictive modeling answers.\n",
    "\n",
    "Predictive modeling can be of two types:\n",
    "- **Regression:** Predicting a continuous numerical value (e.g., predicting a rating score like 3.5 or 4.2).\n",
    "- **Classification:** Predicting a category or class (e.g., predicting whether a customer will return or not).\n",
    "\n",
    "In this project, since our target variable (Overall Rating) is a continuous numerical value, we will perform regression."
